column3: Nigen's brother should have returned from his errand by now.
Find Nigen's brother and slay any enemies that appear.
Hello there, adventurer. There is something I would ask of you if you have the time.
My brother spoke with the udgan for the first time today. The elder gods declared that he must collect his own weight in grass from the field to the southwest.
However, that field is home to many a deadly beast. I want nothing more than to check on his safety, but the gods have said I must cook our family's meals today.
My brother should still be gathering grass to the southwest. Please, go and check on him for me.
My brother should still be gathering grass to the southwest. Please, go and check on him for me.
Th-Thank you. I only let my guard down for a moment, but it was more than enough time for those creatures to attack.
You do not need to accompany me the rest of the way. It is time I proved myself strong enough to carry out what the gods ask of me on my own.
Did you find my brother? He is still yet to return.
Thank you for your help. My brother is returned at last.
We Mol consider the elder gods' orders to be absolute. We must follow them even if it means endangering our lives.
This is a small token of thanks from my brother and I.
